25 LC 33 9751
House Resolution 2
By: Representative Efstration of the 104th
A RESOLUTION
1 Relative to officials, employees, and committees in the House of Representatives; and for
2 other purposes.
3 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that the following
4 provisions shall be in effect during the 2025-2026 biennium of the General Assembly unless
5 and until otherwise provided for by resolution of the House:
6 PART 1
7 SECTION 1-1.
8 (a) Subject to the availability of funds appropriated or otherwise available for the House of
9 Representatives, the Speaker of the House is authorized to employ on behalf of the House
10 of Representatives a sergeant-at-arms, a postmaster or postmistress, assistant postmasters or
11 assistant postmistresses, assistant doorkeepers, pages, aides, secretaries, clerks, court
12 reporters, consultants, and other necessary personnel; and the Speaker is authorized to
13 provide offices for staff services for the House of Representatives and to employ personnel
14 for said offices. The numbers and compensation of personnel so employed pursuant to this
15 section shall be fixed by the Speaker within the limitations of funds appropriated or
16 otherwise available for the operation of the House of Representatives. Personnel employed
