17 pursuant to this section may be employed on a permanent or temporary basis and on a
18 part-time or full-time basis, as may be determined by the Speaker. The assignment and
19 duties of personnel employed pursuant to this section shall be as determined by the Speaker;
20 and any such personnel may be assigned to House officers, committees, committee officers,
21 caucuses, and caucus officers as deemed appropriate by the Speaker, including without
22 limitation assignment of aides to the Speaker Pro Tempore, the Majority Leader, and the
23 Minority Leader.
24 (b) By agreement with the appropriate officer or officers of the Senate, the Speaker of the
25 House may authorize the employment of joint staff and the establishment of joint offices of
26 the General Assembly.
27 SECTION 1-2.
28 The Speaker is also authorized to secure the services of chaplains and interns and provide
29 expense reimbursement allowances for them within the limitations of funds appropriated or
30 otherwise available.
31 SECTION 1-3.
32 The Doorkeeper of the House and the Messenger of the House, who are elected by the
33 House, shall be compensated in an amount to be fixed by the Speaker of the House.
34 PART 2
35 SECTION 2-1.
36 Subject to the availability of funds appropriated or otherwise available for the Clerk of the
37 House's Office, the Clerk of the House is authorized to employ for the Clerk's office assistant
38 clerks, reading clerks, calendar clerks, journal clerks, secretaries, copy readers, clerical
39 assistants, document distributors, audio operators, personnel to distribute bills and other
