40 materials for members, and other necessary personnel. The numbers and compensation of
41 personnel employed pursuant to this section shall be fixed by the Clerk within the limitations
42 of funds appropriated or otherwise available for the operation of the Clerk of the House's
43 Office. Personnel employed pursuant to this section may be employed on a permanent or
44 temporary basis and on a part-time or full-time basis, as may be determined by the Clerk.
45 The assignment and duties of personnel employed pursuant to this section shall be as
46 determined by the Clerk.
47 SECTION 2-2.
48 Pursuant to the provisions of Code Section 28-3-23 of the Official Code of Georgia
49 Annotated, the annual salary of the Clerk of the House shall be as determined by the Speaker.
50 In addition to that amount, the Clerk shall also receive the same percentage salary increase
51 provided in the General Appropriations Act when granted to other employees of the
52 legislative branch of state government. During the Clerk's tenure of office, he or she may,
53 at the discretion of the Speaker, also receive the same expense allowance and the same
54 mileage allowance or travel allowance as received by members of the General Assembly for
55 each day of service rendered by the Clerk.
56 PART 3
57 SECTION 3-1.
58 Subject to the availability of funds appropriated or otherwise available for the operation of
59 the Speaker of the House's Office, the Speaker of the House is authorized to employ interns,
60 aides, secretaries, consultants, and other necessary personnel. The numbers and
61 compensation of personnel employed pursuant to this section shall be fixed by the Speaker
62 within the limitations of funds appropriated or otherwise available for the operation of the
63 Speaker of the House's Office. Personnel employed pursuant to this section may be
