64 employed on a permanent or temporary basis and on a part-time or full-time basis as may be
65 determined by the Speaker. The assignment and duties of personnel employed pursuant to
66 this section shall be as determined by the Speaker.
67 PART 4
68 SECTION 4-1.
69 During any day or period of time during which the General Assembly is not in session,
70 including without limitation any day or period of adjournment during a regular or special
71 session, each of the following officers shall be a committee of one for each day spent on
72 official business: the Speaker of the House, the Speaker Pro Tempore, the Majority Leader,
73 the Majority Whip, the Minority Leader, the Minority Whip, and the Administration Floor
74 Leaders. For each such day spent on official business, each of such officers shall receive the
75 expense, mileage, and travel allowances authorized by law for members of interim
76 committees.
77 SECTION 4-2.
78 (a) During any day or period of time during which the General Assembly is not in session,
79 including without limitation any day or period of adjournment during a regular or special
80 session, each member of the House of Representatives is designated as a committee of one
81 for the purpose of carrying out legislative duties only within the State of Georgia. Subject
82 to any limits established pursuant to Section 5-3 of this resolution, for each such day of
83 service, each member shall receive the expense, mileage, and travel allowances authorized
84 by law for legislative members of interim legislative committees.
85 (b) In addition to the days provided for in subsection (a) of this section and without counting
86 toward the limit specified in said subsection (a), each member of the House is designated as
87 a committee of one for the purpose of carrying out legislative duties on any weekday
