88 which: (1) is a one-day recess or adjournment during a regular session; and (2) occurs after
89 Monday and prior to Friday. For each such day of service, each member shall receive the
90 expense and travel allowances (not including mileage which shall be covered by the weekly
91 round trip) for legislative members of interim legislative committees, if such member has
92 engaged in legislative business on that day, but not otherwise.
93 (c) In addition to the days provided for in subsection (a) of this section and without counting
94 toward the limit specified in said subsection (a), each member of the House is designated as
95 a committee of one for the purpose of attending or responding to any legal matter directly
96 related to his or her legislative duties. For each such day of service or portion thereof, each
97 member shall receive the expense, mileage, and travel allowances authorized by law for
98 legislative members of interim legislative committees. The provisions of this subsection
99 shall also apply to former members and former staff of the House who are attending or
100 responding to any legal matter based on his or her service after the end of his or her term.
101 SECTION 4-3.
102 Pursuant to the provisions of law, in addition to any other compensation they receive as
103 members of the General Assembly, the Majority Leader and the Minority Leader shall
104 receive an amount of $2,400.00 per annum as salary, to be paid in equal monthly or
105 semimonthly installments beginning on the first day of the month following the certification
106 by the caucus of any such election. The Administration Floor Leaders each shall receive an
107 amount of $1,200.00 per annum as salary, to be paid in equal monthly or semimonthly
108 installments. Prior to serving as an Administration Floor Leader, a Representative must be
109 certified as such by the Governor in writing to the Speaker of the House and the Clerk of the
110 House.
