111 PART 5
112 SECTION 5-1.
113 During any period or day of adjournment during a regular or special session, the Speaker is
114 empowered to give authorization for standing committees of the House and such other
115 committees as the Speaker might create to remain at the Capitol during any such period of
116 time for the purpose of considering and studying proposed legislation and other matters.
117 Members of such committees as shall be designated by the Speaker to remain at the Capitol
118 shall receive the expense, mileage, and travel allowances authorized by law for members of
119 interim committees.
120 SECTION 5-2.
121 The Speaker is authorized to appoint committees from the members of the House to serve
122 as interim legislative study committees and for the purpose of performing such duties as the
123 Speaker shall deem necessary. Such committees are authorized to serve during the interim,
124 and the members thereof shall receive the expense, mileage, and travel allowances authorized
125 by law for legislative members of interim legislative committees. The Speaker shall
126 designate the chairperson of any such committee and shall prescribe the time for which any
127 such committee is authorized to function. The Speaker is authorized to extend the time
128 allowed for any committee, whether the committee is created by resolution or by the Speaker.
129 The Speaker is authorized to designate standing committees or any subcommittee thereof to
130 function during the interim for the purpose of performing such duties as the Speaker shall
131 deem necessary. The members of any such committee or subcommittee shall receive the
132 expense, mileage, and travel allowances authorized by law for legislative members of interim
133 legislative committees.
