134 SECTION 5-3.
135 The Speaker shall be authorized to set limits on the number of days per year that a member
136 shall receive the allowances authorized in Sections 4-2 (committee of one) and 5-2
137 (committee meetings during interim) of this resolution. For this purpose a year shall begin
138 on the opening day of a regular session and end on the day prior to the opening day of the
139 next regular session.
140 PART 6
141 SECTION 6-1.
142 The funds necessary to carry out the provisions of Parts 1, 4, and 5 of this resolution shall
143 come from funds appropriated or otherwise available for the operation of the House of
144 Representatives except that funds for any joint staff or joint offices under subsection (b) of
145 Section 1-1 of this resolution shall come from ancillary funds of the General Assembly. The
146 funds necessary to carry out the provisions of Part 2 of this resolution shall come from funds
147 appropriated or otherwise available for the operation of the Clerk of the House's Office. The
148 funds necessary to carry out the provisions of Part 3 of this resolution shall come from funds
149 appropriated or otherwise available for the operation of the Speaker of the House's Office.
150 SECTION 6-2.
151 Any personnel employed pursuant to this resolution shall serve at the pleasure of the
152 appointing authority, and any such personnel may be discharged by the appointing authority
153 with or without cause.
154 SECTION 6-3.
155 This resolution shall take effect immediately upon its adoption by the House of
156 Representatives.
